<!DOCTYPE topic SYSTEM "mingle_help.dtd">
<topic title="User groups page">
  <section title="What you can do on this page">
    <p>The user groups page displays all user groups in the project. All team members can see how many team members are in a user group. Additionally, Mingle administrators and project administrators can:</p>
    <bullets>
      <item>Create a new user group.</item>
      <item>Click on a user group name to <cref topic="user_group_page">modify the team members in the user group</cref>.</item>
      <item>Delete user groups.</item>
    </bullets>
    <screenshot alttext="User groups page" src="resources/images/user_groups_page.png" />
  </section>
  <section title="Also see...">
    <bullets>
      <item><cref topic="user_group_page">Manage team members in a user group</cref></item>
      <item><cref topic="card_transitions#who_can_execute">Limit transitions to team members of specific user groups</cref></item>
      <item><cref topic="managing_project_team_members#manage_user_groups">Add and remove team members from user groups from the team list page</cref></item>
    </bullets>
  </section>
</topic>